</P>
<P>
   ``I know he was a legendary high school distance runner,'' said
Webb, who can tick off Ryun's stats the way other kids can recite
the minutiae of ``Star Wars.'' ``It feels really, really good. It
feels great, actually. When I first did it, it took me a little
while for it to sink in. That night, I was sort of like -- wow!''
</P>
<P>
   Ryun still owns other high school titles. He became the first
high-schooler to break the four-minute mile, running 3:59 when he
was a junior at Wichita East. As a senior, he ran a 3:55.3, still
the American high school record.
</P>
<P>
   But Alan Webb is closing in, and Ryun couldn't be happier.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am thrilled that he broke the record,'' he said. ``The
junior record and senior record, those are still there. It seems
like Alan might be the next possibility, and I wish him well.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
