<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 12:13 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0438 &Cx1f; var-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MAKEOVERS-REVIEW-NYT &LR;      06-26 0707
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MAKEOVERS-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MILLENNIUM MAKEOVERS FOR THE APPEARANCE-CHALLENGED 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For use by special arrangement
only. Asian and European points: Call Karl Horwitz in Paris for
details and prices, phone: 47 42 17 11; fax: 47-42-80-44). Latin
American points: Call Olivia Vasquez in Los Angeles, phone:
310-996-0075; fax: 310-996-0089). 
(lb) 
 By JOE SHARKEY   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   From the Desk of Giancarlo LaMans, Director, Millennium
Makeovers Ltd.:
</P>
<P>
   Face it, friends. If you are appearance-challenged, you are
hitting speed bumps on today's exciting but fiercely competitive
job superhighway, where Youth and Beauty are zooming past in
Ferraris.
</P>
<P>
   You may have seen an article in The New York Times last week
with the headline ``The Chef as Beefcake.'' The message was as
arresting as some of the buff studs pictured, one naked except for
a well-placed blender: A great chef can no longer be just a pudgy,
marginally psychotic tyrant who cooks like an angel. No! Today's
top chef is a sex kitchen utensil who writes cookbooks with titles
like ``Boy Meets Grill.''
</P>
<P>
   Though most of us prefer the cooking staff to be clothed at all
times, that's beside the point. In careers all across America, the
homely, flabby, balding and aged are Out. The young and beautiful
are In. How about that article on the ``aerobic pop-star'' Padre
Marcelo, who's packing the churches in Brazil?
</P>
<P>
   OK, maybe you were born before the Carter administration and
have the silhouette of a sack of potatoes. We here at Millennium
Makeovers are dedicated to the proposition that Sex Appeal boosts
any career! Let me describe a few examples from our great selection
of professional services, available at the more than 250 Millennium
Makeovers Career-Buffing Centers:
</P>
<P>
   BUSMAN'S HOLIDAY: Both Gotham Bus Co. and Alice Kramden would
have been a lot happier if one of Ralph's bright ideas had been to
join Millennium Makeovers' exercise program for those carrying a
wide load. Our staff lead bus drivers in aerobic ``Get on Board,
the Engine's Revved'' sessions. Exact change only. No smoking,
spitting, radio playing!
</P>
<P>
   BYTES `R' US: Intense workout for pasty computer programmers
looking for an upgrade. Graduates receive T-shirts that say ``Giga
Dude'' or ``Giga Gal.''
</P>
<P>
   PUMPED-UP PLUMBERS: Exercise workout for plumbers with an extra
twist: Once they can get their new ``fittings'' in Spandex bike
shorts, they attend self-esteem sessions. Graduates receive a
T-shirt with the slogan ``Plumbers Are Lovers.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, this is all quite interesting, Giancarlo,'' I hear you
say. ``But what if I'm a lazy professional who doesn't want to go
to the gym with bus drivers and computer nerds?'' Not to worry, my
friend! Millennium Makeovers has a marketing staff that is working
overtime just for you.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-JACKET BOFFO: So your new novel reads like F. Scott
Fitzgerald but you look like Barry Fitzgerald. Tired of ending up
on the remaindered table while the crowds elbow past for books with
jacket photos of hunks who, inexplicably, have time to write?
</P>
<P>
   No sweat! We simply sell you a new face for your book jacket,
drawing from our vast archive of Unclaimed Fashion Model and
Theatrical Publicity Photos. Proven results! I'll bet you didn't
suspect that the Post-Feminist Siren-Scribe Naomi Wolf is actually
an 87-year-old former researcher for the WPA Writers Project. Or
that Sebastian Junger, hunkster-author of ``The Perfect Storm,'' is
really a 98-pound weakling who hasn't had a real photo taken since
that unfortunate barracuda accident off Barbados in 1976.
</P>
<P>
   Millennium Makeovers also offers youth-enhancing apparel like:
</P>
<P>
   HABEAS CORPUS: Our ``hip'' line of sexy designer underwear for
that ambitious lawyer who wants to ``court'' new clients. Items can
be personalized with sayings like: ``Sustained!'' or ``Motion?
Here's Your Motion, Pal.''
</P>
<P>
   Wait, there's more! We've produced smash classical music CD
packages like ``Vivaldi Violin Vixens,'' ``Baywatch Beethoven'' and
``The Ring-a-Ding-Ding Cycle'' sung by Frank Sinatra and the Rat
Pack.
</P>
<P>
   ``The fat lady sings?'' Not if Millennium Makeovers can help it!
</P>
</TEXT>
