<HEADER>
A0443 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      06-26 0245
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, June 27 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-MOLD (Los Angeles) _ Her fourth-grade daughter's
headaches and stomach aches grew worse and her grades started
falling, but it wasn't till another child in the class was found to
have high levels of chemicals used in the manufacture of portable
classrooms that this mom put two and two together. The results of a
series of tests ended up worse than she expected _ her little girl
had a poisonous mold growing on her lungs, a mold that has invaded
portables around the state and in Santa Clarita, planted itself in
six patients _ a teacher and five school children _ seen by one
toxicologist. By Pat Aidem. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-SCHOOL-FIASCO- (Los Angeles) _ Long before the Belmont
Learning Center turned into a toxic nightmare for Los Angeles
school officials, it was a dream: an innovative academy for
teen-agers that would be the talk of the nation, a Taj Mahal to
public education. But warning signs were everywhere _ from state
engineers and scientists, from politicians and residents, even the
man who used to own the oil field. All went unheeded. By Terri
Hardy. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
