<P>
   EDUCATION-GOODLING _ WASHINGTON _ As Congress begins a major
overhaul of the law that provides aid to schools, a key policy
maker will be Rep. William Goodling, chairman of the House
Education Committee. After 25 years in the House, most of them in
the minority, the Pennsylvania Republican finally has the chance to
push his ideas on education policy, which have been percolating
since his days as a teacher. (Cox News Service) WITH PHOTOS. EDs:
MOVED Thursday.
