<P>
   BKN-SPURS _ The bizarre NBA season, which began with fans turned
out by the lockout that delayed the tip-off, ends with a group of
nice guys winning the title. The fan-friendly Spurs may help win
back fans. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 20.
</P>
<P>
   BKO-NBADRAFT _ Among underclassmen entering the NBA draft during
the last 5 years, almost none of the undrafted players returned to
college. Just 48.2 percent were drafted. That number has dropped to
43.4 percent the past three years. Only 52 of the 81 players
drafted are still in the NBA. Yet players are leaving college early
_ or are skipping it altogether _ to chase the NBA dream. It has
become such a problem that commissioner David Stern is talking to
the players union about ways to ease the flood. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BKO-CAMP _ Some of the campers don't even remember Mike Glenn as
a former NBA player, but hearing-impaired children from around the
country still flock to his annual one-week camp now held in
Decatur. For the 20th year in a row, the more than 100 campers
experience the fun of basketball and much more. Glenn's father was
a long-time basketball coach and teacher at the Georgia School for
the Deaf. Now he continues the tradition of reaching out to the
hearing-impaired. (Frias, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
