   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-CALLAWAY _ A profile of the rise of LaGrange, Georgia's Eli
Callaway, now the nation's top golf equipment manufacturer.
Callaway's Big Bertha woods and irons are the best-selling clubs on
golf's market. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GLF-WAR _ Callaway is involved with Olimar, another golf
manufacturer, in one of the biggest equipment flaps in golf
history. Both, who claim their brands are superior, are looking
into false advertising. Example: Players they sponsor are playing
with other makes of clubs from Callaway bags. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED
