</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet FOCUS page for the current week. This
story originally moved last week from the Washington Bureau. This
layout is available now.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0626 VOLCANO AFTERMATH _ Four years after a volcano
left the tiny island nation of Montserrat in shambles the tenacious
people of this British territory are rebuilding their lives with an
optimism that belies the seriousness of living with a natural
disaster year after year. (Emling, Cox Washington Bureau). Art
includes 4-column color photo of man taking photos of the volcano
and 2-column photo of new houses under construction.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MONTSERRAT AT A GLANCE _ A fact box profiling island nation. Art
includes photo of city covered with ash in wake of volcano
eruption.
</P>
<P>
   LIVING IN VOLCANO'S SHADOW _ Low expenses and a high quality of
life have brought many from the United States to Montserrat to live
out their version of the American dream. (Emling, Cox Washington
Bureau). Art includes 18-pica color photo of American couple
relaxing near the pool of their spacious Montserrat home.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-GOODLING _ WASHINGTON _ As Congress begins a major
overhaul of the law that provides aid to schools, a key policy
maker will be Rep. William Goodling, chairman of the House
Education Committee. After 25 years in the House, most of them in
the minority, the Pennsylvania Republican finally has the chance to
push his ideas on education policy, which have been percolating
since his days as a teacher. (Cox News Service) WITH PHOTOS. EDs:
MOVED Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   CISNEROS-SCENE _ WASHINGTON _ A look at justice in the Henry
Cisneros case. The case took almost two years to reach trial, in
part because the vast majority of potential jurors don't respond to
summonses. And for all the seriousness of the circumstances, the
judge presides with comedic informality, while rocking vigorously
in his loudly creaking chair and chewing on cups of ice as he
banters with the lawyers. (Malone, Cox News Service). EDs: MOVED
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ With the testimony phase over in the
federal antitrust trial of Microsoft Corp., a look at who seems to
be winning, what comes next, and the prospects of a negotiated
settlement. (Glass, Cox News Service). 25. MOVED in (w) Washington
and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Friday in (w) Washington and (f) Financial
categories.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   GAY-ATLANTA _ ATLANTA _ The banners hanging all over downtown
and Midtown are simple. ``Celebrate,'' they say, over stripes of
different colors that look like a piece of a rainbow or a Life
Savers wrapper. For some, the banners, which are flying for the
first time in three decades of gay pride festival, represent the
growing acceptance and clout of Atlanta's gay community, one of the
country's largest. For others, the message is so simple it's
useless, a reminder, instead, of how far gays and lesbians have to
go before being fully accepted. (Croft/Crenshaw, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
